social_posts.post_text:
✨🌊 The ocean is beautiful, calm, gentle, and moves gracefully in the flow. It can also be terrifying, unpredictable, stormy, and wild. She is powerful beyond measure and inspires awe across humanity. She is a force to be reckoned with - and I want to be like her. 😉

🧜🏻‍♀️ Mermaid Tail: @finfolkproductions 
📸 Photography: @divewithsky

😅🌊 Hurricane Calvin passed through Hawai’i yesterday and we got some heavy rain, wind, and stormy ocean across the islands. Normally I would have stayed dry and cozy on shore, but our girlfriend @sandyseashelbs told us that there was by some miracle good visibility in the water. We obviously had to see it to believe it - and she was right. 😉 

💙 One of the many beautiful things about the ocean is the conditions above the surface are not always reflective of the water below…sometimes you just have to dive in and find out. 

☔️ That said, please DO NOT swim in rough or stormy ocean conditions unless you are a professional or under the supervision of professionals. 🥹🧜🏻‍♀️ #hurricanecalvin #hurricane #mermaid #stormy #underwater 

💖 Mermaid Tail: @finfolkproductions 
📸 Photography: @divewithsky

😅🫧 Can you make it all the way through this underwater cave and up to the surface?

🤿 If not, take a 1.5min break and try again. This time, take 30 seconds before to calm your mind and release any tension in your body. Freediving is about relaxing the mind, body, and spirit. Slow down your thoughts, take a few deep inhale/exhales, and prepare to dive in 3…2..1... ✨Let me know in the comments how you do! ✨

💙 I took the @paditv Freediver course (as well as Padi Advanced Mermaid & Padi Mermaid Instructor course) and it completely changed my technique - I highly recommend to anyone interested in freediving or breathhold!

#freedive #freediving #freediver #holdyourbreath #challenge #underwater #mermaid #gopro 

🧜‍♀️ Mermaid Tail: @finfolkproductions 
📸 Photography: @divewithsky

😍 I am IN LOVE & obsessed with my new silicone tail from @iambraveeer. I was honestly shocked when I opened the package yesterday and saw the most beautiful, sparkly object I have ever laid eyes on. 🧜🏻‍♀️ As this is my first silicone tail (eeek!!!), I was obviously nervous about it fitting me correctly since it’s made to my measurements. But hot damn, this thing fits like a DREAM. It’s a lightweight silicone which makes it so easy to slip into (took me like 45 seconds) and has a really awesome open fluke design so I can pull my @mermaidlinden monofin in and out. 

💅 This is great for me since I do a lot of mermaid shows and need something that’s easy to travel with. I can literally roll it up and put it in a big purse!!!

🌟 And maybe the most insane part of all - IT ARRIVED IN LESS THAN A MONTH!!! Literally 3 weeks after ordering, it was at my doorstep. Thank you so much @iambraveeer!!! 🌟💕😘

📸🤩 Here’s a look at how yesterday’s video was shot!!

🤿 @divewithsky took this vid on our #goprohero11 and despite what a lot of people think, he does not wear a scuba tank when he films me. He is also freediving and his job tends to be a lot harder than mine. 😅

🫧 Not only does he have to hold his breath, but he also has to keep me in frame on the camera while we’re both moving….and I tend to be a very wiley & unpredictable mermaid. 🤣

⚓️ For shots like these, we generally make a rough plan of what we’re going to do before we dive. We very rarely succeed the first time because there are so many factors at play - lighting, framing, body positioning, me being a doofus, etc. 😭

🤭 For every video I post, we’ve done at least 2-3 takes to get it right. Underwater photography is an amazing art and it’s been so fun to see our skills develop!! Hopefully one day we will be true masters. 🧘🏼‍♀️🥋🌊

#gopro #underwater #underwaterphotography #photography #freediving #freediver #behindthscenes

💦🥹 I love how the world above looks from below the surface. The light hitting the water always looks like something out of a beautiful dream. 💫🫧

🌀 It’s such a thin veil that separates these two worlds - the underwater realm and land above. Both places are so full of magic & wonder and yet both are so vastly different. 

🌊 Underwater I feel a sense of true calm & peace. Holding my breath allows me to relax and surrender my mind to the wild & mystical flow of the ocean. My body is weightless and I am free. 🧘🏼‍♀️

☀️🏝️ On land, I can feel the warmth of the sun and the sand between my toes. I feel so connected to the beach, the jungle, the mountains, and the beautiful souls around me on this island. Every step on this soil is a blessing. 🤗

✨ Luckily we can have both!! ✨

🪸 Would you swim this deep in the ocean? Most people I’ve asked say absolutely not 🤣 Butttt….the MAIN reason is always “I would be so afraid of seeing a shark.” 

🦈 Peeps - I am in the water 7 days a week, in the deep ocean, wearing a big fish tail, and I have still never seen a shark in the wild (except cutie reef sharks). And even if I did, it wouldn’t be a big deal because sharks don’t want to eat us. 🤣

☠️ Around 5 people on average are killed by sharks each year. Around 100 MILLION sharks are killed by humans each year. So please don’t be afraid of our shark friends. 

🫧 Instead, educate yourself as to the best way to act when and if you do see a shark. That way you can be empowered by knowledge and learn to spread love for our big fin buddies!

📸 Photography: @divewithsky 
🧜🏻‍♀️ Mermaid Tail: @finfolkproductions

🔱🏛️ Do you believe that Atlantis existed?  I’d love to think a highly advanced, utopian civilization once thrived. In my mind, it was an land of spirituality, science, magic, and morality…and of course there were mermaids hanging around. 🤣

🌟 Many historians and philosophers today still hypothesize about if, when, and where Atlantis could have existed. @divewithsky has been filling me in on some fascinating podcasts he’s listened to from Randall Carlson & Graham Hancock about Atlantis (as well as other ancient cities) and it’s subsequent destruction due to a major climate event around 12,000 years ago. 

🗺️ So much history has been lost to the sands of time. It fascinates me to think about the world that once was!! 

#atlantis #lostcity #mermaid #mermaids

🌟 We all must embark on a journey to find out who we really are….and to do so is to honor the many loved ones that came before us who made our lives possible. And in turn, we will pave the way for future generations that follow.

🫧💫 Living in an underwater fantasy…

🌋 This area in Maui is one of our absolute favorite spots to dive. There is a collection of underwater lava tubes that were formed when Haleakalā (Maui’s big volcano) was erupting into the ocean. 

🪨The lava cooled too quickly as it hit the sea, and formed an incredible collection of sea caves. Each one is totally different and unique. This is one is called “shark cave” because you can often find reef sharks hanging out.

🌟 2024 is only a few days away and I’ve been reflecting on what a crazy year 2023 has been. 

💙 It’s been filled with some incredible highs - like spreading mermaid magic to hundreds of people here on Maui through @mauimermaidschool (and to millions of people on the internet!!), spending each day in the ocean, and sharing beautiful moments with friends. 

💔 To the extreme lows - like the Lahaina (and upcountry) fires destroying countless homes & livelihoods on our island… causing a ripple of sadness & despair across Maui. Over 6,000 residents are still being housed in hotels and unable to find rentals because of our ridiculously expensive & limited housing market. And there is no immediate solution in sight. 

🙏 But life will always be winding and changing, light and dark, high and low - in the end the only way through is forward. In the face of adversity, all we can do is trust our hearts and let intuition guide us.

✨ Sometimes it’s hard to let go of the past - but the journey to happiness begins with taking the first step. 🥹 #2024 #newyear #newyears

🌊 When life gives you a rip current, just keep swimming…🤣

🌀 We were out shooting some underwater vids the other morning, when out of nowhere we got BLASTED by some crazy Kona winds. There were some intense wind waves at the surface and a strong underwater current picked up out of nowhere. 

🫧 We’re all great swimmers so we weren’t worried about getting back, but it definitely felt like being on an underwater treadmill by the end. In this vid you can see me charging the current head-on and not really getting much momentum. (look at how fast the tiny debris is moving!!) 😅

🙌 Surrender your fear of the unknown. None of us can predict the future - even if you try your hardest to prevent the worst outcome of a situation, in the end you will always lose. 

💫 Because in trying to avoid fear & pain, you also close yourself off to the infinite blessings & opportunities that the world can bring your way. 

💙 Only when we remain open-minded, open-hearted, and open to possibility can we overcome our fear of the unknown and become part of the greater flow of the divine, magical, and mystical universe. 🤍

🌟 So let go and jump blindly & bravely into the wilderness of the unknown this new year! It is there you will find true growth, happiness, and freedom. 💦🤗
